Cloud Assignment: Event-Driven Data Processing System
1. Project Overview

This project demonstrates an event-driven data processing system using AWS cloud services. Whenever a JSON file is uploaded to an Amazon S3 bucket, an AWS Lambda function is automatically triggered. The Lambda function processes the employee data and stores it in a DynamoDB table. Another Lambda function retrieves the stored data through API Gateway, which is displayed dynamically on an EC2-hosted website.

2. AWS Services Used
Service	Purpose
Amazon EC2	Hosts the web application
Amazon S3	Stores uploaded employee JSON files
AWS Lambda	Processes uploaded data and retrieves employee records
Amazon DynamoDB	Stores processed employee information
Amazon API Gateway	Provides REST API to the website
IAM	Manages permissions for AWS resources
3. Project Architecture
                User
                  │
                  ▼
         Upload employees.json
                  │
                  ▼
             Amazon S3 Bucket
                  │
        (ObjectCreated Event)
                  │
                  ▼
        ProcessEmployeeData Lambda
                  │
                  ▼
          Amazon DynamoDB
                  ▲
                  │
      get_employees Lambda
                  ▲
                  │
            API Gateway
                  ▲
                  │
          EC2 Hosted Website
4. Workflow
Step 1

The user uploads an employees.json file to the Amazon S3 bucket.

Step 2

The S3 upload event automatically triggers the ProcessEmployeeData Lambda function.

Step 3

The Lambda function reads the JSON file, processes the employee information, and stores it in the DynamoDB Employees table.

Step 4

The website running on Amazon EC2 sends a request to API Gateway.

Step 5

API Gateway invokes the get_employees Lambda function.

Step 6

The Lambda function retrieves employee records from DynamoDB and returns them as JSON.

Step 7

The website displays the employee data dynamically in a table.

